+{"id":"frankenpandas-albra","title":"fd90.153: add gen_feature_parity_table.py to auto-regenerate Phase-2C packet table from artifacts","description":"fd90.74-152 follow-on. fd90.152 added a clarifying note to FEATURE_PARITY.md but flagged auto-regeneration of the Phase-2C Packet Evidence table from artifacts/phase2c/ as out-of-scope for that slice. Pick it up now.

Each artifacts/phase2c/FP-P2[CD]-NNN/ dir has a parity_gate_result.json with structured info:
  {
    'packet_id': 'FP-P2C-001',
    'pass': true,
    'fixture_count': 2,
    'strict_total': 1, 'strict_failed': 0,
    'hardened_total': 1, 'hardened_failed': 0,
    'reasons': []
  }

430 such directories exist. Plan:
1. Add scripts/gen_feature_parity_table.py that:
   - Walks artifacts/phase2c/FP-P2[CD]-*/
   - Reads each parity_gate_result.json
   - Emits a summary count line (X passing / Y total) plus a compact aggregate table
   - Writes to FEATURE_PARITY.md (replacing the static table) or to a new artifact path
2. Keep the script idempotent. Existing scripts/gen_*.py provide the pattern.
3. Test: run the script, verify FEATURE_PARITY.md gains a fresh table with 430 entries (or a compact aggregate by status).
4. Don't break existing parity_gate_check.sh.

